author: Sara Heilman
time required: 45 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}(thinly sliced). Roughly chop @peanuts{1/2%ounce}(roughly chopped). Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced into strips). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(diced). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.

Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Salsa Macha ==

While rice cooks, heat @cooking oil{2%tbsp} in a #small, preferably nonstick, pan{} over medium-low heat. Stir in garlic and @fajita spice blend{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4). Cook, stirring, until garlic begins to crisp and turn lightly golden and spices are fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; carefully transfer to a #medium bowl{} and stir in @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4). Wipe out pan.

Heat @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-low heat. Add peanuts; cook, stirring frequently, until toasted and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Carefully add @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) to pan. Cook, stirring, until vinegar has mostly evaporated, ~{30%seconds} more. Transfer to bowl with garlic oil.

Add @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like; season with @salt{} to taste. Stir to combine.

== Fajita Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and onion and lightly season with @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies begin to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step); cook, stirring, until veggies are lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining Mexican Spice Blend and @salt{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. (TIP: If chicken is browning too quickly, reduce heat to medium.) Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

== Crema ==

Meanwhile, place @sour cream{3%tbsp} in a #small bowl{}. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with chicken and fajita veggies in separate sections; drizzle everything with crema and as much salsa macha as you like.

Garnish with cilantro and serve.

> TIP: Refrigerate any extra salsa macha in an airtight container for up to 3 days.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.